{{Unreferenced|date=September 2009}}

The '''2009 [[TUMS Fast Relief 500]]''' was the 32nd race of the [[2009 NASCAR Sprint Cup Series|2009 NASCAR Sprint Cup season]] at the beginning of the second half of the [[2009 Chase for the Sprint Cup]]. The 500-lap, {{convert|263|mi|km}} event, the only race on the Chase that is held on a short track ({{convert|.526|mi|km}}), was held on October 25, 2009 at [[Martinsville Speedway]] in [[Martinsville, Virginia]]. [[Denny Hamlin]] won; points leader [[Jimmie Johnson]] finished second.

